{% extends "core/emails/base.html.j2" %}
{% block title %}Your quick start guide - sbomify{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
    <h1>Your quick start guide, {{ user.first_name|default:user.username }}!</h1>
    <p>Getting started with sbomify is easy. Here's how to get your first SBOM up and running:</p>
    <h2>3 Simple Steps</h2>
    <ul class="feature-list">
        <li>
            <strong>Create a product</strong> for your software (e.g., "My Web App")
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Add a component</strong> for each piece you want to track
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Upload an SBOM</strong> using our
            <a href="https://github.com/sbomify/sbomify-action" target="_blank">GitHub Action</a>
            or upload one manually
        </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        Once your SBOM is uploaded, head over to Plugins to enable vulnerability
        scanning and compliance checks.
    </p>
    <p style="text-align: center; margin: 32px 0;">
        <a href="{{ app_base_url }}/dashboard" class="button">Go to Dashboard</a>
    </p>
    <div class="highlight-box">
        <h3>Pro Tip</h3>
        <p>
            Our GitHub Action generates and uploads SBOMs automatically with every push
            or release. Set it up once and your SBOMs stay current without any manual work.
        </p>
    </div>
    <p>
        Want to learn more? Check out our <a href="https://sbomify.com/faq">FAQ</a>.
        Got questions? Just reply to this email.
    </p>
{% endblock %}
